'''Jan Paul van Hecke''' (born 8 June 2000) is a Dutch professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for {{English football updater|Brigh&HA}} club [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] and the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands national team]].

==Club career==

=== Early career ===
Born in [[Arnemuiden]],<ref name="wf" /> Van Hecke is a youth product of [[VV Goes]], but signed for [[NAC Breda]] in 2018.<ref name="voetbalprimeur">{{Cite web |date=10 September 2020 |title=Volgende Heerenveen-deal krijgt vorm: Van Hecke verlaat NAC Breda |url=https://www.voetbalprimeur.nl/nieuws/944171/volgende-heerenveen-deal-krijgt-vorm-van-hecke-verlaat-nac-breda.html |access-date=4 March 2021 |website=voetbalprimeur.nl |language=nl-NL}}</ref> He made his professional debut with NAC Breda in a 5–1 [[Eerste Divisie]] win over [[Helmond Sport]] on 16 August 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2019/08/16/netherlands/eerste-divisie/nac-bv/stichting-helmond-sport/3031685/|title=NAC Breda vs. Helmond Sport – 16 August 2019 – Soccerway|website=uk.soccerway.com}}</ref>

===Brighton & Hove Albion===
On 10 September 2020, Van Hecke joined [[Premier League]] side [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] on a three-year contract.<ref name="voetbalprimeur" /><ref>{{Cite web |last=Owen |first=Brian |date=10 September 2020 |title=Albion confirm deal – and line up a loan – for rising Dutch defender van Hecke |url=https://www.theargus.co.uk/sport/18712607.albion-sign-defender-jan-paul-van-hecke/ |access-date=4 March 2021 |website=The Argus |language=en}}</ref>

====Loans====
On 18 September 2020, he returned to the Netherlands on a season-long loan with [[Eredivisie]] side [[SC Heerenveen|Heerenveen]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Camillin |first=Paul |date=18 September 2020 |title=Van Hecke loaned to Heerenveen |url=https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/1833307/van-hecke-loaned-to-heerenveen |access-date=4 March 2021 |website=www.brightonandhovealbion.com |publisher=Brighton & Hove Albion F.C. |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=18 September 2020 |title=Heerenveen huurt Van Hecke van Brighton, nieuwe spelverdeler voor ADO |url=https://nos.nl/l/2348847 |access-date=4 March 2021 |website=Nederlandse Omroep Stichting |language=nl}}</ref> He made his debut for Heerenveen in a 3–1 Eredivisie win away to [[Fortuna Sittard]] on 19 September 2020.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Owen |first=Brian |date=20 September 2020 |title='Powerful' young Albion defender is off to great start on loan |url=https://www.theargus.co.uk/sport/18734201.albion-defender-jan-paul-van-hecke-enjoys-debut-win/ |access-date=4 March 2021 |website=The Argus |language=en}}</ref>

On 29 August 2021, he joined [[Blackburn Rovers F.C.|Blackburn Rovers]] of the [[EFL Championship|Championship]] on loan for the [[2021–22 Blackburn Rovers F.C. season|2021–22 season]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Rovers swoop for Seagulls star |date=29 August 2021 |url=https://www.rovers.co.uk/news/2021/august/Rovers-swoop-for-Seagulls-star/ |publisher=Blackburn Rovers Official Site |access-date=29 August 2021}}</ref> He made his debut on 16 October, playing the whole match of the 2–2 home draw against [[Coventry City F.C.|Coventry City]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Blackburn Rovers 2–2 Coventry City: Sky Blues fight back from two goals down – BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/58853029|publisher=BBC Sport|date=16 October 2021|access-date=16 October 2021}}</ref> He was sent off for a reckless challenge on [[Harry Wilson (footballer, born 1997)|Harry Wilson]] on his fifth appearance with Rovers already 2–0 down in an eventual 7–0 defeat at home to [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] on 3 November.<ref>{{cite web |title=Blackburn Rovers 0–7 Fulham: Free-scoring Cottagers hit seven at Ewood Park – BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/59059048|publisher=BBC Sport|date=3 November 2021|access-date=3 November 2021}}</ref> Van Hecke scored his first goal for Blackburn and in English football, doubling Rovers' lead with a powerful header in a 2–0 away win at second placed [[AFC Bournemouth]] on 11 December, closing the gap to four points to their promotion rivals.<ref>{{cite web |title=Bournemouth 0–2 Blackburn |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/59529343|publisher=BBC Sport|date=11 December 2021|access-date=11 December 2021}}</ref> He was named as the club's Player of the Season for 2021–22, becoming the first loanee to achieve the accolade.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |last=Sharpe |first=Rich |title=Jan Paul van Hecke thanks fans as he is named player of the year |url=https://www.lancashiretelegraph.co.uk/sport/20107225.brighton-duo-scoop-blackburn-rovers-end-season-awards/ |access-date=2 May 2022 |website=Lancashire Telegraph |date=May 2022 |language=en}}</ref>

====Breakthrough with Brighton====
[[File:BHA 5 v Espanyol 1 pre season 30 07 2022 154 (Jan Paul van Hecke) (cropped1).jpg|thumb|left|200px|Van Hecke with [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] in 2022.]]

Van Hecke made his debut for Brighton on 24 August 2022, helping keep a clean sheet in the 3–0 away victory over [[EFL League One|League One]] side [[Forest Green Rovers F.C.|Forest Green Rovers]] in the [[2022–23 EFL Cup|EFL Cup]] second round.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/62571845|title=Forest Green 0–3 Brighton: Albion to face Arsenal in third round – BBC Sport|publisher=BBC Sport Sport|date=24 August 2022|access-date=2 September 2022}}</ref> Three days later, he made his [[Premier League]] debut, coming on as a 88th minute substitute for [[Danny Welbeck]] and helped secure Brighton's 1–0 lead over [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] to take all three points at [[Falmer Stadium]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Howarth |first=Matthew|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/62614441|title=Brighton & Hove Albion 1–0 Leeds United: Pascel Gross strikes as Seagulls set club record – BBC Sport|publisher=BBC Sport|date=27 August 2022|access-date=2 September 2022}}</ref> With the absence of [[Levi Colwill]], Van Hecke was selected ahead of [[Adam Webster (footballer, born 1995)|Adam Webster]] where he made his first Premier League start on 21 January 2023, in the 2–2 away draw at [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Talbot |first=Bruce|url=https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/3031868/its-fergie-time-as-evans-late-leveller-lifts-albion|title=It's Fergie time as Evan's late leveller lifts Albion|publisher=Brighton & Hove Albion|date=21 January 2023|access-date=21 January 2023}}</ref> He played in the 1–1 home draw against champions [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] on 24 May, keeping [[Erling Haaland]] goalless with Brighton sealing a place in the [[2023–24 UEFA Europa League]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/65290302|title=Brighton 1–1 Manchester City: Julio Enciso scores stunning equaliser to seal Europa League place|publisher=BBC Sport|date=24 May 2023|access-date=24 May 2023}}</ref>

On 13 July 2023, Van Hecke signed a new contract with the Seagulls; the length of the contract was undisclosed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/articles/cj5nrqdnlv1o|title=Van Hecke signs new Brighton deal|date=13 July 2023}}</ref>

In the [[2023–24 Brighton & Hove Albion F.C. season|2023–24 season]], Van Hecke began to establish himself as a regular member of the starting eleven, finishing the season with 28 Premier League appearances and five [[Shutout|clean sheets]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Jan Paul van Hecke {{!}} Football Stats {{!}} Brighton & Hove Albion {{!}} Season 2022/2023 {{!}} Soccer Base |url=https://www.soccerbase.com/players/player.sd?player_id=116885&season_id=155 |access-date=2024-08-27 |website=www.soccerbase.com}}</ref> He was rewarded for his form with a new contract until 2027, with head coach [[Roberto De Zerbi]] praising Van Hecke for his performances, saying that he is "improving in an incredible way".<ref>{{Cite web |date=18 January 2024 |title=Brighton: 'The most improved player under De Zerbi' |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/articles/cl505j8qd11o |access-date=2024-08-27 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

==International career==
Van Hecke was called up to the [[Netherlands national under-21 football team|Netherlands under-21]] squad for the first time in March 2022,<ref>{{cite web |title=Who's on international duty this break?|url=https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/2545301/whos-on-international-duty-this-break|publisher=Brighton & Hove Albion|date=21 March 2022|access-date=21 March 2022}}</ref> but was an unused substitute in a 0–0 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualifying draw against [[Bulgaria national under-21 football team|Bulgaria]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Bulgaria U21 vs. Netherlands U21 – Football Match Line-Ups – March 25, 2022 – ESPN |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/lineups/_/gameId/601159 |access-date=2 May 2022 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref> He made his debut for the under-21 side on 3 June, coming on as a substitute in the 3–0 away win over [[Moldova national under-21 football team|Moldova under-21s]] in a [[2023 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification|2023 European under-21 Championship qualifier]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Live Commentary – Moldova U21 vs Netherlands U21 – 03.06.2022 |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/Moldova-U21-vs-Netherlands-U21/460325|date=3 June 2022|access-date=6 June 2022 |website=Sky Sports |language=en}}</ref>

On 16 August 2024, Van Hecke was named in the 35-man provisional [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] squad for the [[UEFA Nations League|Nations League]] ties against [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] and [[Germany national football team|Germany]] alongside Brighton teammates [[Bart Verbruggen]] and [[Mats Wieffer]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=16 August 2024 |title=New faces named in provisional Netherlands squad |url=http://www.football-oranje.com/new-faces-named-in-provisional-netherlands-squad/ |access-date=2024-08-27 |website=Football Oranje |language=en-US |author1=Admin }}</ref> He was originally left out of the final squad but received his first senior call up on 1 September after the withdrawal of [[Micky van de Ven]] due to injury.<ref>{{Cite web |date=30 August 2024 |title=Hato and Timber named in Netherlands squad |url=https://www.football-oranje.com/hato-and-timber-named-in-netherlands-squad/ |access-date=2024-09-01 |website=Football Oranje |language=en-US |author1=Admin }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=1 September 2024 |title=Van Hecke replaces injured Van de Ven in Netherlands squad |url=http://www.football-oranje.com/van-hecke-replaces-injured-van-de-ven-in-netherlands-squad/ |access-date=2024-09-02 |website=Football Oranje |language=en-US}}</ref> He debuted on 10 September 2024 against Germany at [[Johan Cruyff Arena]]. He substituted [[Matthijs de Ligt]] at half-time of a 2–2 draw.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/698930/germany-netherlands|title=Netherlands v Germany game report|date=10 September 2024}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Van Hecke is the nephew of the Dutch retired footballer [[Jan Poortvliet]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Boogert |first=Rudy |date=2 November 2020 |title=Jan Paul van Hecke kan niet tippen aan ome Jan |url=https://www.pzc.nl/amateurvoetbal/jan-paul-van-hecke-kan-niet-tippen-aan-ome-jan~ad10f33a/ |access-date=4 March 2021 |website=Provinciale Zeeuwse Courant |language=nl}}</ref>

